75  devices, you can define the device in your toolchain compiler preprocessor.

79  - Ultra Low Power Medium-density Plus devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and
80  STM32L162xx microcontrollers where the Flash memory density is 256 Kbytes.
81  - Ultra Low Power High-density devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and STM32L162xx

284 #if defined ( __CC_ARM )
285 /* ARM Compiler
286  ------------
287  RAM functions are defined using the toolchain options.
288  Functions that are executed in RAM should reside in a separate source
289  module. Using the 'Options for File' dialog you can simply change the
290  'Code / Const' area of a module to a memory space in physical RAM.
291  Available memory areas are declared in the 'Target' tab of the
292  'Options for Target' dialog.
293 */
294  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
295 
296 #elif defined ( __ICCARM__ )
297 /* ICCARM Compiler
298  ---------------
299  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain keyword "__ramfunc".
300 */
301  #define __RAM_FUNC __ramfunc FLASH_Status
302 
303 #elif defined ( __GNUC__ )
304 /* GNU Compiler
305  ------------
306  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain attribute
307  "__attribute__((section(".data")))".
308 */
309  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status __attribute__((section(".data")))
310 
311 #elif defined ( __TASKING__ )
312 /* TASKING Compiler
313  ----------------
314  RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain pragma. This pragma is
315  defined in the stm32l1xx_flash_ramfunc.c
316 */
317  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status
318 
319 #endif

876 #define SRAM_BB_BASE ((uint32_t)0x22000000)
